e bullet-train thesis.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Kevin Warsh Remarks\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Productivity Framework:\u003c/strong\u003e Warsh is aggressively promoting AI as the \u0026quot;most productivity-enhancing wave of our lifetimes,\u0026quot; arguing this allows for rate cuts even at full employment.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe 12-Month Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Markets are beginning to price the structural cut within a new Chair\u0026#39;s first 12 months, targeting a sharp repricing before end of Q4. Treat as narrative, not confirmed policy guidance.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix:\u003c/strong\u003e The mega-trend breakout (daily candle taking the monthly high) validated on May 1st continues to provide the structural wind at the back of the bull trend.\u003c/div\u003e\n  